The concept of „comparative literature” in various traditions. The survey of the history of the discipline. Contemporary methods of comparative analysis.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course traces the history of the concept of „comparative literature” and its meanings in various traditions and gives a historical overview of the discipline. It introduces the students to the problems of intertextuality, comparative poetics and cultural typology, with a particular emphasis on text translation, exchange and transfer in culture. Finally, the course offers the opportunities of comparative analysis of literature, arts, media and scientific discourse.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  To introduce students to the history of the discipline, to teach methods of comparative analysis.
